24 Feb 2010 17:44






Promising, for the reasons Laranos mentions. The numbering of ants is wayyy too specific- it's fine that the amount increases exponentially, but not even the Foundation is going to count all 78,125 ants to make sure they're multiplying precisely. Round to the nearest hundred and it will still convey "lots of ants!!"

This could definitely benefit from some test logs. They could explore some of the big unanswered questions: Where are they ants coming from? Do they literally appear out of nowhere? Someone could fail to notice a few ants getting onto their body, but they'd definitely see it happening with hundreds. What if the person is wearing a skin-tight suit, or submerged in water, or doused with RAID? The Foundation would probably try at least a few of these things.







